Torin and Gatara assist in the unloading, while Riekan keeps his hand 
planted firmly on Phoenix's shoulder, his harpoon gun at the ready.

For the first time, Phoenix looks up.  An expression of childlike 
wonder crosses her face as she sees the outdoors for what she thinks 
is the first time.  But she's a little confused, because it all 
vaugely reminds her of something ... something that occasionally 
flashes through her dreams ...

--- In nbwrpg@y..., "dewboy30816" <dewboy30816@y...> wrote:
> Flicker wants to rush over to her, but realizes it would not be for 
> the best, so he begins unloading quickly.
> 
> --- In nbwrpg@y..., "cardhead649" <cardhead649@y...> wrote:
> > Gatara activates a remote control as she lands, decloaking the 
ship 
> > and allowing Flicker his first good look.  It's not nearly as big 
> as 
> > a battleship, but the latter would have a rough time fighting the 
> > former - Rogue Star bristles with assorted weaponry, not all of 
it 
> > Cybertronian in origin.
> > 
> > "Personally, I don't care about the rubber duck.  You'll see her, 
> all 
> > right," she tells him, "but she's staying right here until 
exactly 
> > half your ship's cargo is aboard Rogue Star.  Riekan!  Jayde!  
> > Torin!  Let's go, already!"
> > 
> > The two males tramp out of the ship, with Phoenix between them, 
> head 
> > down.  She's a mess - she hasn't seen the inside of a CR chamber 
in 
> a 
> > long time.  There's no sign of the other Rogue.
> > 
> > "Well, where's Jayde?" Gatara asks, irritated.
> > 
> > "Last I saw, she was in her sister's room," Torin explained.
> > 
> > Gatara rolls her eyes.  "That explains it.  Alright, let's get 
this 
> > stuff unloaded."
